								<h3><span style="color: #3973AC;">Results</span></h3>
								<p>All results will be anonymized. Personal information will remain strictly confidential.</p>
								<p>The anonymized results of the study will be made available on the CALIPER website to allow for open worldwide access. The data will also be published in reputable international journals. This wide dissemination of the results is aimed to help with their use in children hospitals across Canada and worldwide, as well as for purposes of public education.</p>
								<p>The CALIPER project has been in operation since 2006. The project has established or is in the process of establishing reference intervals for a large number of blood tests commonly performed in the clinical laboratory. The reference intervals provided for these blood tests are specific for a child’s age and sex and also for several ethnic groups.</p>
								<p>The CALIPER project is an ongoing project. Determining of reference intervals for a wider selection of blood tests are in development. Currently, reference intervals are provided specific for age, sex, and several ethnic groups, where this is necessary. As more data becomes available, reference intervals may also be established for additional ethnic groups. Specific reference intervals may also be provided according to child’s height, weight or developmental stage.</p>
